body_html:
www.tensorflow.org is more commonly referred to as our frontpage, or main page.

Anyway, the issue is caused by release tag update. Looks like we did not have a successful build since the latest release. Once all the build issues are resolved, the links will be back.
When there are issues such as this, you can always click the build history and manually download a binary from the latest successful run. In this case, if you modify the version string from 1.2.0rc2 to 1.2.0rc1, it should work.

body:
`www.tensorflow.org` is more commonly referred to as our frontpage, or main page.

Anyway, the issue is caused by release tag update. Looks like we did not have a successful build since the latest release. Once all the build issues are resolved, the links will be back.
When there are issues such as this, you can always click the build history and manually download  a binary from the latest successful run. In this case, if you modify the version string from `1.2.0rc2` to `1.2.0rc1`, it should work.
